Encapsulation
===============
->Binding the data and its operation of an entity is known as encapsulation
*.jar file is a encapsulation of package
*.package is a encapsulation of classes
*.classes is a encapsulation of varable and method


real time of encapsulation
---------------------------
java bean file
*.class  must be public 
*.class member must be private
*.custractor must be public
*.public getter and setter

program to understand encapsulation
-------------------------------------
import java.util.*;
public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Student s=new Student();
       s.setId(101);
       s.setName("janvi");
       s.setAddress("hsr");
       System.out.println(s.getId()+" "+s.getName()+" "+s.getAddress());
        
    }
}
class Student{
 private int id;
   private String name;
   private String address;
   Student(){
       
   }
  public  Student(int id,String name,String address){
      this.id=id;
      this.name=name;
      this.address=address;
  }
  public int getId(){
      return id;
  }
  public void setId(int id){
      this.id=id;
  }
  public String getName(){
      return name;
  }
  public void setName(String name){
      this.name=name;
  }
  public String  getAddress(){
      return address;
  }
  public void setAddress(String address){
      this.address=address;
  }
    
}
